name: Venous
description: It was painted during a lecture on Anatomy and Physiology of the Cardiovascular System of my friend who had always been curious about the Venous blood, also known as deoxygenated blood. Some people thought it was blue in color, but we all know there has never been a blue blood. That's why she came up with the idea of what if the blue colored blood is truly true and decided to paint this masterpiece.
